South Africa&#39;s rand firmed more than 1.5 percent against the US dollar on Tuesday on rumours that the African National Congress (ANC) will discuss the removal of President Jacob Zuma at a major party meeting. An ANC spokesperson said the rumours were a &quot;complete fabrication&quot;. The rand firmed to 13.0175 per dollar, its firmest since April 25, according to Thomson Reuters data. By 1257 GMT, it had retreated to 13.0850/dollar, 1.21 percent firmer than its overnight close.